@startuml fig-udp-session-ack-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title UDP session management with token and acknowledgement

participant "Client\n:9300 (ephemeral)" as C #FFE0B2
participant "Server\nUDP :9300" as S #C8E6C9

== SESSION ESTABLISHMENT ==

C -[#1565C0]> S : HELLO
S -[#43A047]-> C : TOKEN:a3f8b1c2

note over S
  Server generates a unique token
  and stores it with seq=0.
end note

== DATA EXCHANGE ==

C -[#1565C0]> S : MSG:a3f8b1c2:message 1
S -[#43A047]-> C : ACK:a3f8b1c2:1

C -[#1565C0]> S : MSG:a3f8b1c2:message 2
S -[#43A047]-> C : ACK:a3f8b1c2:2

C -[#1565C0]> S : MSG:a3f8b1c2:message 3
S -[#43A047]-> C : ACK:a3f8b1c2:3

== ERROR HANDLING ==

C -[#E53935]> S : MSG:invalid_tok:text
S -[#E53935]-> C : ERR:TOKEN

C -[#E53935]> S : MSG:bad_format
S -[#E53935]-> C : ERR:FORMAT

legend right
  UDP provides no session state natively.
  The application layer implements:
  1. Session via HELLO / TOKEN exchange
  2. Sequencing via server-side counter
  3. Acknowledgement via ACK replies
  4. Error signalling via ERR messages
endlegend
@enduml
